      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. Let's get down to the brass tacks of your travel conundrum. When faced with a canceled flight, the goal is to minimize your total travel time, and this can depend on several factors including the availability of flights, the time of day, and the airlines' schedules.\n\nRebooking a single long flight through a hub like Dubai can be a good option if there are direct flights available. This can potentially save you time compared to a multi-stop route, as it reduces the number of times you have to go through security and boarding processes. However, this also depends on the flight schedules and the time it takes to transfer from one flight to another.\n\nOn the other hand, a multi-stop route through Doha or Dubai might be quicker if there are more frequent flights available and if the individual legs are shorter. This can also be a good option if there are no direct flights available from Heathrow to Singapore. However, this option might require more time spent in transit and at the airports.\n\nIn general, it is recommended to check the flight schedules and availability of flights from Heathrow to Singapore, as well as the flight schedules and availability of flights from Heathrow to Dubai or Doha. This will help you determine which option is statistically better",
